Document: GLTFAnimation
Path: godot/classes/class_gltfanimation.rst
Summary: Methods for retrieving and storing arbitrary data associated with GLTFDocumentExtension classes in GLTFAnimation instances.

Method: get_additional_data(extension_name: StringName) → Variant
Gets additional arbitrary data stored in this GLTFAnimation instance. Used to keep per-node state data in GLTFDocumentExtension classes, which are stateless by nature. The extension_name parameter should be the name of the GLTFDocumentExtension (does not need to match the extension name in the glTF file). Returns the stored Variant value or null if no data was set.

Method: set_additional_data(extension_name: StringName, additional_data: Variant) → void
Sets arbitrary data in this GLTFAnimation instance for use with GLTFDocumentExtension classes. The first parameter is the GLTFDocumentExtension name (does not need to match the glTF file's extension name), and the second parameter can be any Variant value. This allows storing per-node state information in stateless extension classes.